description:
Subjects Addressed: (1) This prophecy was given to king Hezekiah. 2 Kings 20:17,18. (2:30)
(2) The fulfillment of the prophecy took place in the fourth generation. Approximately 99 years had elapsed since the prophecy was given. Daniel 1:1-3. (3:30)
(3) The first siege took place under the leadership of king Jehoiakim, because of the following reasons. 2 Kings 24:3,4. Discover the sins of Manasseh. 2 Kings 21:2-4,16.(13:50)
(4) Discover the meaning of the shedding of innocent blood by Manasseh, Jehoiakim, and SDA leaders today. (21:30)
(5) Hezekiah and Hephzibah knew that captivity was coming, yet did not prepare their son, Manasseh. (31:50)
(6) Manasseh rebuilt the high places, which represent false education. (39:20)
(7) Discover the meaning of allowing yourself or your children to pass through the fire as did Manasseh and Jehoiakim. (44:50)
(8) Discover the events that transpired under the first siege. Similar things are happening now that proves we are under the first siege. (58:00)
(9) The first thing that Nebuchadnezzar did during the first siege was to impart to the Hebrews the education of Babylon, government sponsored education. SDAs sought and received accreditation from the government in the years leading up to 1931. (1:02:00)
(10) Discover the characteristics of Daniel and the three Hebrews, along with the fact that they received the experience of the first angel’s message. (1:16:50)
(11) Daniel and the three Hebrews rejected Government approved education, diet, and lifestyle (Eunuchs); as a result they were favored by God. (1:25:40)
(12) Daniel and the three Hebrews received a double blessing from the Lord in order to witness and win the king of Babylon to true worship. (1:41:41)
(13) What king Hezekiah failed to do, in witnessing to the leaders of Babylon approximately 99 years before, Daniel and the three Hebrews accomplished. (1:39:50)
